---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ToolPageCta from '../../components/ToolPageCta.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import AdUnit from '../../components/AdUnit.astro';

const gitconfigExample = `[core]
    pager = delta

[interactive]
    diffFilter = delta --color-only

[delta]
    navigate = true          # use n and N to move between diff sections
    side-by-side = true      # enable side-by-side view
    line-numbers = true      # show line numbers
    syntax-theme = Dracula   # pick from bat's theme list
    hyperlinks = true        # clickable file paths in supported terminals

[merge]
    conflictstyle = diff3

[diff]
    colorMoved = default`;

const faq = [
  { question: "What is delta?", answer: "delta (git-delta) is a syntax-highlighting pager for git diff and git log output, written in Rust by Dan Milstein. It replaces the default less pager with a rich terminal viewer that adds syntax-highlighted code, line numbers, side-by-side diffs, themed output, and clickable hyperlinks. You configure it once in .gitconfig and it enhances every git diff, git show, and git log -p command automatically." },
  { question: "How do I configure delta with git?", answer: "Add these lines to your ~/.gitconfig: [core] pager = delta. Also add [interactive] diffFilter = delta --color-only so that git add -p and interactive staging also use delta. Then add a [delta] section to configure options like side-by-side = true, line-numbers = true, and syntax-theme. Run 'delta --list-syntax-themes' to see available themes." },
  { question: "How does delta compare to diff-so-fancy?", answer: "diff-so-fancy is a shell script that post-processes git diff output to make it more readable. delta is a compiled Rust binary that acts as the pager itself. delta is significantly faster, has true syntax highlighting (via the same library as bat), native side-by-side diff mode, line number support, hyperlinks, and is actively maintained. diff-so-fancy's main advantage is that it's a pure shell script with no binary dependency. Most developers who try both prefer delta." },
  { question: "How do I choose a delta theme?", answer: "Run 'delta --list-syntax-themes' to see all available themes (they come from bat's theme list). You can preview themes by running 'delta --show-syntax-themes'. Popular choices include Dracula, GitHub (light-friendly), Nord, OneHalfDark, and TwoDark. Set your choice with 'syntax-theme = ThemeName' in the [delta] section of .gitconfig. You can also set 'dark = true' or 'light = true' to toggle delta's UI chrome independently from the syntax theme." },
  { question: "Can I use delta without git, for regular diff files?", answer: "Yes. delta reads from stdin and outputs to stdout, so you can pipe any diff output through it: 'diff -u file1.txt file2.txt | delta'. You can also pass delta a patch file directly: 'delta < my.patch'. This makes it useful for reviewing any unified diff format, not just git diffs." },
  { question: "Does delta work on Windows?", answer: "Yes. Install delta via Cargo ('cargo install git-delta'), Scoop ('scoop install delta'), or download a binary from the GitHub releases page. Configure .gitconfig the same way as on macOS/Linux. Delta works in Windows Terminal, PowerShell, and Git Bash." },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="delta — Syntax-Highlighting Git Diff Viewer for the Terminal"
  description="delta (git-delta) is a Rust-based syntax-highlighting pager for git diff output. Get side-by-side diffs, line numbers, themes, and hyperlinks in your terminal. Configure once in .gitconfig."
  tool="delta git diff, git-delta, syntax highlighting diff, git pager, diff-so-fancy alternative, side-by-side git diff"
  faq={faq}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "name": "delta — Syntax-Highlighting Git Diff Viewer for the Terminal",
    "url": "https://devplaybook.cc/tools/delta",
    "description": "delta (git-delta) is a Rust-based syntax-highlighting pager for git diff output. Get side-by-side diffs, line numbers, themes, and hyperlinks.",
  })} />

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">delta</h1>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-6">
    A <strong>syntax-highlighting pager for git diff</strong> output, written in Rust.
    Configure delta once in your <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded text-sm">.gitconfig</code> and every
    <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded text-sm">git diff</code>, <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded text-sm">git show</code>,
    and <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded text-sm">git log -p</code> command becomes beautifully readable.
  </p>

  <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 text-sm text-text-muted flex-wrap">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Syntax highlighting via bat</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Side-by-side diffs</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Line numbers</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Written in Rust (fast)</span>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">What is delta?</h2>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-4 leading-relaxed">
    delta (published as the <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded text-xs">git-delta</code> crate) is a pager replacement for Git that transforms raw diff output into a rich, readable terminal display. It uses the same syntax highlighting library as <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded text-xs">bat</code> to color code hunks by language, adds line numbers, supports true side-by-side layout, and even renders hyperlinks to file paths in supporting terminals.
  </p>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-4 leading-relaxed">
    Once you set <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded text-xs">pager = delta</code> in your <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded text-xs">.gitconfig</code>, delta enhances every git command that pages output — no extra flags needed. It also integrates with <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded text-xs">git add -p</code> interactive staging via the <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded text-xs">diffFilter</code> setting.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Key Features</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-muted space-y-1 mb-4 ml-2">
    <li><strong>Syntax highlighting</strong> — colors added/removed lines by language using bat's Syntect-based highlighting</li>
    <li><strong>Side-by-side diffs</strong> — view old and new versions in parallel columns instead of interleaved</li>
    <li><strong>Line numbers</strong> — show original and new file line numbers in the margin</li>
    <li><strong>Theme support</strong> — dozens of themes (Dracula, Nord, GitHub, OneHalfDark, and more)</li>
    <li><strong>Navigate mode</strong> — use 'n' / 'N' to jump between diff sections like a search result</li>
    <li><strong>Hyperlinks</strong> — clickable file paths in terminals that support OSC 8 hyperlinks</li>
    <li><strong>diff-so-fancy integration</strong> — can mimic diff-so-fancy style for a gradual migration</li>
    <li><strong>git blame</strong> — enhanced blame output with syntax highlighting and configurable layout</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Installation</h2>
  <pre class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-4 text-xs font-mono overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre text-text mb-2"># macOS (Homebrew)
brew install git-delta

# Rust / Cargo (any platform)
cargo install git-delta

# Windows (Scoop)
scoop install delta

# Windows (winget)
winget install dandavison.delta

# Linux (apt — Ubuntu/Debian)
# Download .deb from: https://github.com/dandavison/delta/releases
dpkg -i git-delta_*.deb</pre>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Recommended .gitconfig</h2>
  <pre class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-4 text-xs font-mono overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre text-text mb-4" set:html={gitconfigExample}></pre>
  <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-4">After saving, run <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded">git diff HEAD~1</code> to see delta in action. Run <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded">delta --list-syntax-themes</code> to pick a theme.</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">delta vs diff-so-fancy</h2>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
    <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr class="bg-bg-card">
          <th class="border border-border px-3 py-2 text-left">Feature</th>
          <th class="border border-border px-3 py-2 text-left">delta</th>
          <th class="border border-border px-3 py-2 text-left">diff-so-fancy</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">Implementation</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">Rust binary</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">Shell script (Perl)</td></tr>
        <tr class="bg-bg-card/30"><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">Syntax highlighting</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2 text-green-400">Yes (Syntect)</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">No</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">Side-by-side diffs</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2 text-green-400">Yes</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">No</td></tr>
        <tr class="bg-bg-card/30"><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">Line numbers</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2 text-green-400">Yes</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">No</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">Navigate mode</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2 text-green-400">Yes</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">No</td></tr>
        <tr class="bg-bg-card/30"><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">No binary dependency</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">Requires binary</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2 text-green-400">Shell script only</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">Performance</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2 text-green-400">Excellent (Rust)</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">Good</td></tr>
        <tr class="bg-bg-card/30"><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">Active maintenance</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2 text-green-400">Yes</td><td class="border border-border px-3 py-2">Slowing</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Use Cases</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-muted space-y-1 mb-4 ml-2">
    <li>Reviewing pull request diffs locally before pushing</li>
    <li>Code review sessions in the terminal for remote servers without GUI access</li>
    <li>Improving readability of <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded text-xs">git log -p</code> for understanding change history</li>
    <li>Reviewing patch files from email-based Git workflows</li>
    <li>Enhancing <code class="bg-bg-card px-1 rounded text-xs">git add -p</code> interactive staging with highlighted hunks</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Pros and Cons</h2>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
    <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-400 mb-2">Pros</h3>
      <ul class="text-text-muted text-sm space-y-1">
        <li>✓ Dramatically improves diff readability</li>
        <li>✓ True syntax highlighting per language</li>
        <li>✓ Side-by-side mode for easy comparison</li>
        <li>✓ Fast Rust binary with minimal overhead</li>
        <li>✓ One-time .gitconfig setup, then automatic</li>
        <li>✓ Works with all git commands that use a pager</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-400 mb-2">Cons</h3>
      <ul class="text-text-muted text-sm space-y-1">
        <li>✗ Requires binary installation (no shell-only option)</li>
        <li>✗ Side-by-side mode needs a wide terminal window</li>
        <li>✗ Some theme configurations require manual tuning</li>
        <li>✗ Adds a dependency to dotfiles/bootstrap scripts</li>
        <li>✗ Hyperlinks require a supporting terminal emulator</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <AdUnit slot="auto" format="auto" label="Advertisement" />
  <FaqSection faq={faq} />
  <ToolPageCta currentTool="delta" relatedTags={['git', 'cli', 'terminal', 'devops', 'version-control']} />
</BaseLayout>
